        <article style="font-size:20px">Since 6.30 WIB on Friday (4/26/2019), the water on the Ciliwung River has risen rapidly. Status Siaga 1 began to be set at 20:30 last night, making potential flooded areas on alert. Thus was reported from Liputan6, Tribunnews.com, and Tirto.id.<br><br>The overflow of water on the Ciliwung River causes flooding and inundation at a number of points in Jakarta. The volume of river water increases due to rain in Bogor, West Java, on Thursday (04/25/2019), so that it is brought to Jakarta.<br><br>One of the most affected is the Bidara Cina, Jatinegara, East Jakarta area, which reaches 3 meters high. There were 2 fatalities carried away by the flood. DKI BPBD noted, the location of floods included the South Jakarta area namely RW07 Lenteng Agung Village, RW01 Srengseng Sawah Village, RW01 Pengadegan Village, RW07 Rawajati Village, RW (05, 06, 07, 08) Pejaten Timur Village, with a flood height of about 20 cm up to 170 cm.<br><br>While the East Jakarta area includes RW (02, 05, 08) Cawang Village, RW05 Balekambang Village, RW (04, 05, 08) Kampung Melayu Village, RW (07, 11) Bidara Cina Village. The Aksi Cepat Tanggap Volunteer Team (ACT) , visited the Bidara China area, to evacuate. Around 05.00 WIB, the water began to rise with a height reaching 1.5 to 2 meters.<br><br>There are still residents who have not been displaced. Some of the houses were submerged to reach the roof of the house, even the roof of the house was almost submerged. Some residents choose to be on the house for their security<br><br>Let's take part in relieving your burden from the floods in Jakarta and surrounding areas !!</article>
